  "text": "To understand what this momentum sector is, let us consider the root configurations of the Halperin (330) and the Z 4 parafermion states. First, the Halperin (330) state is constructed as the direct product between two Laughlin states in the top (↑) and bottom (↓) layers, each of which has three degenerate copies via the centerof-mass shift, leading to the nine-fold ground-state degeneracy of the Halperin (330) state [CITATION_1] . Specifically, the Laughlin state has the following three root configurations:",
